  "texts": [
    "The data of R median Hα are also available in the dataset of this work (see Appendix E).",
    "Figure 5 shows the distributions of the derived R Hα values with stellar effective temperature for the spectra (in Figure 5a) and stellar sources (in Figure 5b) in the MRS time-domain sample of solar-like stars employed in this work.",
    "Each dot in Figure 5a corresponds to a MRS spectrum, and the R Hα values from the multiple observations of the same stellar source are connected by a vertical line segment; as a reference, Figure 5b displays the R Hα distribution for the stellar sources by using the R median Hα values (each dot corresponding to a stellar source).",
    "As exhibited in Figure 5, for the MRS time-domain sample employed in this work, the R Hα values is on the order of magnitude of 10 -5.",
    "The median of δR Hα (uncertainties of the R Hα values) is about 1.4 × 10 -7, which is shown as an error bar (±δR Hα) in the bottom right corner of the diagrams in Figure 5."
  ],
